[
    {
        "content": "<p>I understand that when one wants to place two different structures of the same kind on the same type, and there is already one instance of the structure as a type class, then one (recommended?) way is to form a type synonym. Apparently one should be able to \"copy\" other relevant instances to the type synonym by <code>@derive</code>, but replace the instance that one wants to get rid of by something else. This sounds fine and well, but I had some issues with the syntax...</p>\n<p>(Btw, sorry, I might have technicalities wrong above. Please point out mistakes you notice and I will correct to make this as generally useful to new members as possible.)</p>",
        "id": 247092154,
        "sender_full_name": "Kalle KytÃ¶lÃ¤",
        "timestamp": 1627159280
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here is an example, in which I would like to introduce the weak topology on a normed space <code>E</code> --- instead of the default topology <code>instance</code> on <code>E</code>, which is the norm topology. My attempt below is to create a type synonym <code>weak E</code> (in fact <code>weak ğ•œ E</code> since I struggled with implicit arguments) which is just <code>E</code>, but will instead be equipped with the weak topology. I would also like <code>weak E</code> to inherit the same old <code>add_comm_group</code> and <code>module ğ•œ</code> from <code>E</code> (it is only the topology I want to get rid of).</p>",
        "id": 247092159,
        "sender_full_name": "Kalle KytÃ¶lÃ¤",
        "timestamp": 1627159293
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is an approximate <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a> (the two questions are pretty much right at the start, the rest is included for context). As a summary, my two questions are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to <code>derive</code> a <code>module ğ•œ</code> structure on <code>weak ğ•œ E</code>?</li>\n<li>How to get rid of using <code>@to_weak</code> with lots of <code>_</code>s?<ul>\n<li>(The other direction, <code>to_ordinary</code>, seems to work just fine without the <code>@</code>!)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">tactic</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">analysis.normed_space.dual</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[derive add_comm_group]</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- Q : `@[derive [add_comm_group, module ğ•œ]]` fails. How to state?</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/-- The canonical map `E â†’ weak ğ•œ E`. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/-- The canonical map `weak ğ•œ E â†’ E`. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_weak_injective</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">function.injective</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary_injective</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">function.injective</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"bp\">Î»</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[simp]</span> <span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_weak_to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[simp]</span> <span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary_to_weak</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n  <span class=\"c1\">-- Q : Without the `@`-notation and lots of `_`s, the statement doesn't parse. How to fix?</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[simp]</span> <span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_weak_inj_iff</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"bp\">@</span><span class=\"n\">to_weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">_</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†”</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">iff.rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[simp]</span> <span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary_inj_iff</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†”</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">iff.rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">attribute</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">irreducible</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/-- The type-level equivalence between `E` and `weak ğ•œ E`. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">equiv_to_weak</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">nondiscrete_normed_field</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_group</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">normed_space</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"bp\">â‰ƒ</span> <span class=\"n\">weak</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">E</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">{</span> <span class=\"n\">to_fun</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">to_weak</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">inv_fun</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">to_ordinary</s